  "texts": [
    "Fig. 6 shows the Pareto fronts for all methods.",
    "Across both benchmarks and different metrics, DIVERSE-VAR consistently defines the frontier, underscoring that our scale-travel effectively refines the output image quality while retaining the diversity introduced by condition-annealing.",
    "CFG scheduling increases the diversity but also significantly degrades the image quality.",
    "Injecting noise into the text embedding or <SOS> token enhances diversity beyond what CFG scheduling can offer, by preventing the dominance of the conditioning signal during early generation steps.",
    "Among these condition-annealing techniques, noise injection to the text embedding yields the best diversity-quality trade-off, yet results in clear quality degradation-as shown in the sharp drop in the Pareto front as diversity increases."
  ],
